ISLAND ONE (part 2 of 6):<br>
<br>
a.)<br>
<br>
NOTHING on the isle is agro on you when you arrive there and this Isle is usually doable by 9 to 12 people.<br>
DON’T use any AE spells ( no AE stun , mezz , or procs or something else ).IF you use it you agro the efreetis in the quest hall on you which will kill you in one or two seconds.<br>
<br>
b.) <br>
The mobs :<br>
<br>
1.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The Keymaster : <br>
<br>
He is a dwarf in full plate armor and is a merchant. He will never join any fight and is always indifferently to you. He sells coffins , Key of swords ( this key would port u Noble Dojorns Isle if u use it on the west platform ) , Key of Veeshan ( this key costs one copper and will port u into the quest hall on isle 1 when u use it on the north platform ) , a box of void ( 1pp , no clue about the use of this item , weight 8,7 and has 2 slots and a combine button ) , Mana batteries class 1 to 5 ( class 5 costs 1501pp ).<br>
<br>
If u attack him he will punch for 2054 damage per hit.<br>
<br>
Btw…we already tried several theories with the use of those mana batteries and the box of void like combining 2 mana batteries , combining 2 keys and also 2 turned in keys , tried to leave the zone with the keys in the box….nothing worked so far…although there are some more theories ( u can take the box out of the zone btw ). All additionally information is very welcome.<br>
<br>
2.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 8 spirits :<br>
<br>
They hit for 160 max and cast a low level enchanter DoT ( choke ) , They have also a damage shield on them and need to be debuffed . There are 8 of the spirits and at symmetric spawn points on the first isle.<br>
ALL of the 8 spirit drop 3 “ rabbit feets “ and 3 “ miniature swords “ ( 24  swords and feets altogether ) and a random tessera for a specific class which is part of the sky quests<br>
<br>
3.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The spirit princess :<br>
<br>
She hits for up to 250 damage per hit and casts also choke as DoT. She spawns next to the Keymaster in the center of the isle. She drops rarely a nice item ( so far there droped an enchanter bracer , 2 SK haste belts , 1 rogue haste belt on this server) or just nothing ( sometimes even fishing grubs *grins * ).After she is killed there spawns immediately and halfling NPC ( Sirran the Lunartic ) .<br>
<br>
4.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Sirran the Lunartic :<br>
<br>
He is a halfling NPC and if u attack him he punches also for 2054 . When u give him the “ miniature swords “ and the “ rabbit feets “ ( it doesn’t matter if u give both together or step by step ) u will get from him a  ‘ Horn ‘ for the “rabbit feet” ( looks like a minotaur horn but forgot the name ) and the “ key of swords “ for the “miniature sword “. He will spawn on ALL islands in the zone after u killed each boss from each island to turn in the specific key components to get the correct keys for a further isle.Btw..NEVER say hassle to him or he will attack you.<br>
<br>
5.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 16 named Efreetis :<br>
<br>
Those are in the quest hall and aren’t supposed to be killed I think .There u can get the books for the quests and also finish all the quests. Also the Fiery Avenger quest starts here.<br>
<br>
c.)<br>
<br>
The keys u get on isle one are : <br>
<br>
1.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The rabbit feet’s ; these will not disappear when u log , die in the zone or go LD in the zone. The feet’s will poof when u LEAVE the zone. When you give these feets to the halfling NPC u will get a horn which is the key u need to use on the east platform to teleport to the Imp isle.<br>
<br>
2.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The horn u get from the rabbit feets will disappear when u go LD , when you die or leave the zone. This Horn will summon u to the imp isle by using it on the east teleport platform on the first isle.<br>
<br>
3.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The miniature sword : this key has the same rules like the rabbit feets . You will get the Key of swords from the halfling for it.<br>
<br>
4.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The Key of swords : It will port u on Noble Dojorns isle. This key will also poof when you go LD , die or leave the zone ( like the horn key ).<br>
<br>
5.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The key of veeshan : it will just port you into the quest hall and is only buyable at the keymaster.<br>
<br>
<br>
TACTIC :<br>
<br>
As soon as the groups arrived we will move to the east corner on the eastern teleport platform. We will kill the spirit there and pull 4 more spirits step by step to that corner to avoid other spirits or even the princess joining the fight. When 5 of them are killed we move to the west corner on the western teleport platform and kill also the spirit there and pull the last 2 spirits step by step to there and kill them.<br>
At this point there will have been dropped 24 rabbit feet’s and 24 miniature swords. All of the 24 people NEED to have one rabbit feet at this point.<br>
The last mob to kill is the spirit princess in the center isle. We will kill her and log out…DON’T turn in the rabbit feet’s yet to the halfling.<br>
At Saturday when the other 12 to 24 people port up we will clear the isle again to provide the extra 12 to 24 people also with rabbit feets . As soon as the princess is dead then and the halfling spawned u will turn your rabbit feet in for the horn. ALL people in the raid will need to do that ( groupleaders will make sure all in their group will have done it ).<br>
When u have ur horn u move to the east side of the isle plz and wait with your group there to summon over ( plz make sure u aren’t to close together to keep the chances to go LD low as possible ).<br>
IF somebody goes LD we will need to buy him a key to make it possible to port him over to imp isle then.<br>
All of u will have a key for the imp isle at this point. We will buff up and port over after the scout on the imp isle ( who will be a monk or rogue ) gave us green light.<br>
